createJobConfigurationAddon

JobConfigurationAddon createJobConfigurationAddon(java.lang.String ID,
                                                  YouScopeClientConnection client,
                                                  YouScopeServer server)
Returns a new job configuration addon for the given ID, or null if addon does not support the configuration of jobs with the given ID.

Parameters:
ID - The ID for which a job should be created.
client - Interface to allow the addon to communicate with the client.
server - Interface to the server.
Returns:
The created addon to configure a job.

getConfigurationClass

java.lang.Class<? extends JobConfigurationDTO> getConfigurationClass(java.lang.String ID)
Returns the implementation (not an interface) of the configurations produced by the addon with the given ID, or null, if this addon does not support the configuration of jobs with the given ID. YouScope uses the class definition internally to obtain information about the functionality (=implemented interfaces) of the respective configuration, e.g. to search for job configurations with a given functionality.

Parameters:
ID - The ID for which a job should be created.
Returns:
The class of the job implementation, or null.

getSupportedConfigurationIDs

java.lang.String[] getSupportedConfigurationIDs()
Returns a list of all job configuration types supported by this addon

Returns:
List of supported configurations.

supportsConfigurationID

boolean supportsConfigurationID(java.lang.String ID)
Returns true if this addon supports job configurations with the given ID, false otherwise.

Parameters:
ID - The ID of the job configuration for which it should be queried if this addon supports its construction.
Returns:
True if this addon supports job configurations with the given ID, false otherwise.

getJobName

java.lang.String getJobName(java.lang.String ID)
Should return a short human readable name of the job which corresponds to the given ID. If the addon does not support the configuration of jobs with the given ID, null should be returned. The name may or may not consist of sub-strings separated by slashes (e.g. "Misc/Foo"). The last string corresponds to the base name. In this case, a client may or may not display some kind of folder structure to navigate to a given addon.

Parameters:
ID - The ID of the job for which the human readable name should be returned.
Returns:
Human readable name of the job.

getJobIcon

javax.swing.ImageIcon getJobIcon(java.lang.String ID)
Returns an icon for this job, or null, if this job does not have an own icon.

Parameters:
ID - The ID of the job for which the icon should be returned.
Returns:
Icon for the job, or null.
